"><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Schematic overview 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Real example 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-D938907F-A9CA-4203-9C03-01BEF2F64543" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-67012A74-7DB0-405F-8CE6-5F30133BD303-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-67012A74-7DB0-405F-8CE6-5F30133BD303-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-EAA56381-D4E6-4F69-A3A9-D9D43E4E4B98" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6A03A799-204D-4253-995D-9ACE3384CA1E-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6A03A799-204D-4253-995D-9ACE3384CA1E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-EC1EAE23-40EC-4B10-A2C9-83873F76DC70" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Symptoms (What do you see)</b> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Sharp difference in gloss between swaths at the edges of the print
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Alternating pattern visible (inverted on the other side of the print)
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> - Visibility is depended on the width of the print (more visible in wide prints)
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Only visible in equal step print mode/strategy
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-F15EB8DE-4305-49A1-911E-24D389B3B6C3" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional logging (if available)</title><p class="- topic/p ">No logging available which can pinpoint to this case.
</p></section><section id="GUID-7276E98F-D711-4B0E-9C9C-ABAE886EB159" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ADAM-triggers</title><p class="- topic/p ">No ADAM-triggers available. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><fig id="GUID-62EC67FD-66B9-492D-95BA-FB60F03ED458" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4E7D55D9-9D4C-48B9-B050-57E49F38F77A-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4E7D55D9-9D4C-48B9-B050-57E49F38F77A-svg.svg"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-BB9BDDD1-E29C-42C5-BF10-2854E3AE4223" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Steps explanation</title><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-D963269B-E108-446A-A212-4581FEAA8740" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="4" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="20*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col4" colnum="4" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Type 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">To do 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Decision 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check whether the possibility exists to switch to a Stamping or mono-directional print mode/strategy. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">The possibility is depended on the type of Colorado (eg : C1630, C1650, ..)
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Select Stamping or mono-directional print mode/strategy
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Check possibility to print in portrait mode instead of landscape mode (rotate image 90°) 
</p></entry><entry colname="col4" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">Zebra banding only exists in an equal step printmode/Strategy. Use other print modes/strategies.. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p ">After ink has been jetted on the media is starts to spread. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The amount of spreading determines the finishing appearance on the final cured print. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">When the carriage is changing directions at the edge of the print the time difference between the current and the next swath is short, therefore the amount of spreading between the swaths is almost equal. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">At the other side of the current swath the difference between the current and previous swath is longer, so a difference in spreading can be seen.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-BDE42A10-0DAA-46D3-99F7-D18695E3843E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
